_Pu’al_ Active Participle for Regular Shorushim:
The [[{{_pu’al_ active participle}} form]] has the following conjugation pattern for [[regular shorushim]]:
|            | *Masculine* | *Feminine* |
| *Singular* | מְזֻמָּן <br> _mezumon_ <br> [he is] being invited | מְזֻמֶּנֶת <br> _mezumenes_ <br> [she is] being invited |
| *Plural*   | מְזֻמָּנִים <br> _mezumonim_ <br> [those men are] being invited | מְזֻמָּנוֹת <br> _mezumonois_ <br> [those women are] being invited |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
